# Multi-Agent Infrastructure

# Introduction

Multi-Agent Infrastructure is one of the most advanced areas in modern LLMOps and Generative AI engineering.

Instead of using a single LLM for every task, multi-agent systems use:
- Multiple AI agents
- Specialized workflows
- Tool orchestration
- Memory systems
- Autonomous reasoning

to solve:
- Complex enterprise tasks
- Multi-step reasoning
- Autonomous workflows
- AI automation systems

---

# What is an AI Agent?

An AI agent is a system that can:
- Reason
- Plan
- Use tools
- Access memory
- Make decisions
- Execute tasks autonomously

---

# Traditional LLM vs AI Agent

| Traditional LLM | AI Agent |
|---|---|
| Single response | Multi-step execution |
| Stateless | Stateful workflows |
| No planning | Autonomous reasoning |
| Limited tooling | Dynamic tool usage |

---

# Multi-Agent Systems

Multi-agent systems involve:
- Multiple cooperating AI agents

working together to complete tasks.

---

# Example

```text
